<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Memory-Management on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/memory-management/</link><description>Recent content in Memory-Management on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/memory-management/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Double Free or Corruption — Freeing Already-Freed Memory Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-double-free-or-corruption--freeing-already-freed-memory-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Double Free or Corruption — Freeing Already-Freed Memory Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;double free or corruption&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; error occurs when your program attempts to &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; a pointer that has already been freed, or when it frees a pointer that was never allocated on the heap. This corrupts the heap metadata used by the memory allocator, which can cause crashes, data corruption, or exploitable security vulnerabilities. The error message typically reads &lt;code&gt;double free or corruption (fasttop)&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;double free or corruption (!prev)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C ARC Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-arc-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-arc-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ARC errors occur when Objective-C code violates Automatic Reference Counting rules or has incorrect memory management patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using retain/release/autorelease under ARC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect bridge casts between ObjC and Core Foundation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assigning to ivar without proper ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mixing ARC and non-ARC code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circular strong references&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Don&amp;#39;t call retain/release under ARC
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// [object retain]; // WRONG
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// [object release]; // WRONG
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use proper bridge casts
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CFStringRef cfString &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (__bridge_retained CFStringRef)nsString; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// +1 ref
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CFRelease(cfString); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Balance
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use weak for delegates
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@property&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nonatomic&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;weak&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;MyDelegate&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; delegate;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use __block to avoid retain cycles in blocks
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;__block&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt; weakSelf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; self;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;self.block &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt; strongSelf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; weakSelf;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [strongSelf doWork];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C Block Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-block-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-block-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Block errors occur when Objective-C blocks capture variables incorrectly, create retain cycles, or access variables out of scope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong reference cycles between blocks and objects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capturing self strongly in blocks (creating retain cycles)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accessing variables after they go out of scope&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect block copy semantics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modifying captured variables without __block qualifier&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use __weak to avoid retain cycles
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;__weak&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;typeof&lt;/span&gt;(self) weakSelf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; self;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;self.completionBlock &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;__strong&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;typeof&lt;/span&gt;(weakSelf) strongSelf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; weakSelf;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [strongSelf doWork];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use __block for mutable captured variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;__block&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; counter &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;increment)(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; counter&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;++&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Copy blocks to heap when needed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Block_copy(myBlock);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C Memory Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-memory-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-memory-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Memory errors occur when Objective-C code accesses memory it shouldn&amp;rsquo;t, leaks memory, or has incorrect retain/release patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accessing deallocated objects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retain cycles causing memory leaks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using MRC (Manual Reference Counting) incorrectly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buffer overflows in C-level code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect use of __bridge casts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use weak references to break retain cycles
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@property&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nonatomic&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;weak&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt; delegate;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use ARC (Automatic Reference Counting)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// @property (nonatomic, strong) NSString *name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Check for memory issues with Instruments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use Address Sanitizer in Xcode scheme settings
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Proper bridge casts
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CFStringRef cfString &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;__bridge&lt;/span&gt; CFStringRef)nsString;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C Message Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-message-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-message-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Message errors occur when an Objective-C object receives a message it cannot respond to, or when memory has been freed before the message arrives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling a method not declared in the object&amp;rsquo;s interface&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in method name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using a protocol without implementing required methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Object deallocated before message delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect method signature between declaration and implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Declare methods in header file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt; : &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;NSObject&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;- (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;myMethod&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Verify protocol conformance
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt; : &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;NSObject&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;MyProtocol&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Must implement all required @protocol methods
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use performSelector for dynamic dispatch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ([object respondsToSelector:&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@selector&lt;/span&gt;(myMethod)]) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [object performSelector:&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@selector&lt;/span&gt;(myMethod)];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C MRC Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-mrc-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-mrc-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MRC errors occur in legacy Objective-C code using manual retain/release, leading to memory leaks or crashes from incorrect reference counting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing retain/release calls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Over-releasing objects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not retaining objects stored in collections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect autorelease pool usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accessing ivar after release&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Retain objects you want to keep
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;self.myObject &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; [[MyObject alloc] init]; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Retains
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Release in dealloc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;- (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;dealloc&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [_myObject &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;release&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [super dealloc];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use autorelease for temporary objects
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NSString &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;temp &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; [[[NSString alloc] initWithFormat:&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;@&amp;#34;Hello %@&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name] autorelease];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use NSAutoreleasePool for loops
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NSAutoreleasePool &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;pool &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; [[NSAutoreleasePool alloc] init];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Code creating autoreleased objects
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[pool drain];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Objective-C Runtime Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-runtime-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/objective-c/objc-runtime-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Runtime errors occur when the Objective-C runtime encounters an invalid operation during program execution, typically involving message passing or memory management issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sending a message to a nil object&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling an undefined method on an object&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Memory corruption from incorrect retain/release cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accessing deallocated memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mismatched method signatures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-objectivec" data-lang="objectivec"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Check for nil before sending messages
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (object &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; nil) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [object doSomething];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use respondsToSelector for optional methods
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ([object respondsToSelector:&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@selector&lt;/span&gt;(optionalMethod)]) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [object optionalMethod];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use @try/@catch for exception handling
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; [object riskyOperation];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;@catch&lt;/span&gt; (NSException &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;exception) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; NSLog(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;@&amp;#34;Exception: %@&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, exception.reason);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Swift Memory Error — Heap Corruption Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/memory-error-swift/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/memory-error-swift/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="memory-error--heap-corruption--memory-error"&gt;Memory Error — Heap Corruption / Memory Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Memory errors occur when Swift&amp;rsquo;s memory management is violated, leading to crashes, corruption, or unexpected behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swift uses Automatic Reference Counting (ARC) for memory management. Memory errors happen when references are incorrectly managed, leading to use-after-free, double-free, or heap corruption.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retain cycles&lt;/strong&gt; — strong reference cycles between objects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use after free&lt;/strong&gt; — accessing deallocated memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unmanaged memory&lt;/strong&gt; — unsafe pointer operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Buffer overflow&lt;/strong&gt; — writing beyond allocated memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Retain cycle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ViewController&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; closure: (() -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; closure = {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;.doSomething() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Strong capture of self&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Unsafe pointer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; ptr = UnsafeMutablePointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.pointee = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.deallocate()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(ptr.pointee) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use after free&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Buffer overflow&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; buffer = UnsafeMutableBufferPointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Buffer overflow&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Double free&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; ptr = UnsafeMutablePointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.deallocate()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.deallocate() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Double free&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-weak-self"&gt;Fix 1: Use weak self&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ViewController&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; closure: (() -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; closure = {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;.doSomething()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ViewController&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; closure: (() -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; closure = { [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;weak&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;?.doSomething()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-unowned-for-non-optional-references"&gt;Fix 2: Use unowned for non-optional references&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ViewController&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; closure: (() -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; closure = {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;.doSomething()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ViewController&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; closure: (() -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; closure = { [&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;unowned&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;.doSomething()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-defer-for-cleanup"&gt;Fix 3: Use defer for cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; ptr = UnsafeMutablePointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.pointee = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use ptr&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.deallocate()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; ptr = UnsafeMutablePointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;defer&lt;/span&gt; { ptr.deallocate() }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ptr.pointee = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use ptr&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-withunsafemutablebufferpointer"&gt;Fix 4: Use withUnsafeMutableBufferPointer&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; buffer = UnsafeMutableBufferPointer&amp;lt;Int&amp;gt;.allocate(capacity: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;buffer.deallocate()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; count = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; result = [Int](unsafeUninitializedCapacity: count) { buffer, initializedCount &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; buffer[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;] = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; initializedCount = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Avoiding retain cycle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;NetworkManager&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; completionHandler: ((Data?) -&amp;gt; Void)?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetchData&lt;/span&gt;() {
